related_items.title: Drawing the line
description: 1 drawing. | World War II cartoon shows Under Secretary of State Sumner Welles addressing two men in sombreros labeled "Argentina" and "Chile," both sitting on a fence.  Welles has drawn a line on the ground, one side labeled "Our Friends" and one "Our Enemies."  Argentina and Chile were the only two Latin American countries to refuse to join the United States in breaking off relations with the Axis Powers.  In October 1942, Welles accused them of allowing Axis agents to use their territory to pursue hostile activities against their neighbors.  Despite American pressure, neither country broke relations with Germany until the closing days of the war.
